# Configuration Management
YAML configuration is assumed as the central configuration to the Framework.
Example:
url: "https://practice.expandtesting.com/notes/app/login"
api_url: "https://practice.expandtesting.com/notes/api"
email: "your_email"
password: "your_password"
grid_url: "http://localhost:4444/wd/hub"
run_on_grid: true
# Setup Instructions
# Step 1 — Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/Akshayavelma2/NotesApp_Appliction_Testing.git
Click on Step 2 button.Click on Step 2 — Go To Project Folder.
cd NotesApp_Appliction_Testing
Now we will be creating a virtual environment.Let's create a virtual environment now.
python -m venv myvenv
Start the virtual environment.Start the virtual environment.Turn on the Virtual Environment.
myvenv\Scripts\activate
# Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
# Test Execution
# Execute Complete Framework
pytest
# Parallel Execution
pytest -n 2
# Execute Specific Test
pytest tests/test_login.py

# Allure Reporting
# Generate Allure Results


pytest tests --alluredir=allure-results


# Generate Report

allure generate allure-results -o allure-report --clean
# Open Report

allure open allure-report

# Selenium Grid Execution
# Start Selenium Grid


docker run -d ^
--name selenium-grid ^
-p 4444:4444 ^
-p 7900:7900 ^
--shm-size="2g" ^
selenium/standalone-chrome:latest

# Verify Grid

Open:

http://localhost:4444

Perform tests on a grid.Perform tests on a grid.
pytest -n 2

# Jenkins CI/CD

